00:35:13,150 --> 00:35:18,874
that we simply couldn't let slide, and then educate those on the team who needed more

467
00:35:18,874 --> 00:35:26,500
insight into the specialist knowledge required to fix the problem. So it was a ton of hard

468
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:27,221
work, but it was totally worth it.

469
00:35:27,221 --> 00:35:33,246
So speaking of hard work, and to close out this section on the technological chops of

470
00:35:33,246 --> 00:35:38,470
Uncharted 2, I wanted to quickly come back to the subject of our train level.

471
00:35:39,493 --> 00:35:43,655
Like I said, the train was one of the first levels that we started on

472
00:35:43,655 --> 00:35:48,977
and one of the last levels that got finished.

473
00:35:48,977 --> 00:35:51,198
And to be frank, it was an evil monster of a level to create.

474
00:35:51,198 --> 00:35:54,960
In our train level, there is a train of 50 separate train cars

475
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:59,401
that are really moving along through our streaming environments

476
00:35:59,401 --> 00:36:00,242
at a pretty good lick.

477
00:36:01,167 --> 00:36:05,149
uh... you could see all fifty cars at pretty much anytime during the level

478
00:36:05,149 --> 00:36:09,270
uh... and when we first started building the level when you looked at the first

479
00:36:09,270 --> 00:36:10,611
car from the last car

480
00:36:10,611 --> 00:36:16,173
the little lamp hanging on the front of the first car was still swinging

481
00:36:16,173 --> 00:36:20,855
we had developed but we haven't really used uh... a level of detail system for

