00:36:20,855 --> 00:36:21,895
the first uncharted

483
00:36:21,895 --> 00:36:26,097
uh... but the train certainly made us put it into action in double quick time

484
00:36:26,097 --> 00:36:27,077
as i'm sure you can imagine

485
00:36:29,376 --> 00:36:33,978
Now we had as a design goal that the train should only progress in the world

486
00:36:33,978 --> 00:36:36,119
if you were progressing along it.

487
00:36:36,119 --> 00:36:41,242
And in order to make this happen we had to do a lot of weird stuff.

488
00:36:41,242 --> 00:36:44,304
Sometimes teleporting the train into new positions

489
00:36:44,304 --> 00:36:47,145
depending on what you did and where you died.

490
00:36:47,145 --> 00:36:51,027
And this along with just the general craziness of the whole idea of doing a

491
00:36:51,027 --> 00:36:53,248
train for real like this

492
00:36:53,248 --> 00:36:55,189
led to a lot of bugs as you can imagine.

493
00:36:55,189 --> 00:36:57,590
Particularly with the enemy's navigational systems.

494
00:36:58,244 --> 00:37:04,448
they would get really confused every time the train teleported for instance

495
00:37:04,448 --> 00:37:07,770
uh... also for a long time when you shot the enemies and they dropped their

496
00:37:07,770 --> 00:37:08,151
weapons

497
00:37:08,151 --> 00:37:12,834
the weapon would zoom back off down the track where you come from

498
00:37:12,834 --> 00:37:15,596
as it shifted into the coordinate system of the world

499
00:37:15,596 --> 00:37:17,437
even better than that grenades

500
00:37:17,437 --> 00:37:20,439
would fly back in your face and blow you up after you'd thrown them

501
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:26,094
To cap things off, at one point we realized that the player's gun aiming

502
00:37:26,094 --> 00:37:27,216
raycasts

