00:38:58,555 --> 00:39:02,418
In fact, we'd had such a good experience making the multiplayer part of Uncharted 2

528
00:39:02,418 --> 00:39:07,460
that we think that we would now not want to make a game that didn't have some kind of multiplayer

529
00:39:07,460 --> 00:39:13,544
or at least networked capability, since it's such a good way for us to connect with our community of players

530
00:39:13,544 --> 00:39:16,866
and because it affords so many interesting game design opportunities.

531
00:39:18,758 --> 00:39:23,179
In order to create our multiplayer game, all we did was simply take Nathan Drake's moveset

532
00:39:23,179 --> 00:39:28,321
from the single player game and implemented it in a competitive multiplayer environment.

533
00:39:28,321 --> 00:39:32,882
And we were delighted, by the way, that it immediately felt right.

534
00:39:32,882 --> 00:39:37,443
We devised a whole bunch of different game types, building outwards from pretty simple

