00:50:50,593 --> 00:50:53,535
difficulty spikes, we had to scramble to add additional

681
00:50:53,535 --> 00:50:55,016
sanity check playtests right up to just days

682
00:50:55,016 --> 00:50:55,416
before Gold Master.

683
00:50:55,416 --> 00:50:57,638
Doing the playtests in-house was the only way that running

684
00:50:57,638 --> 00:50:58,939
so many tests was possible.

685
00:51:06,889 --> 00:51:10,091
especially when a lot of them took place at short notice.

686
00:51:10,091 --> 00:51:12,172
And it also had the enormous benefit

687
00:51:12,172 --> 00:51:15,394
of allowing all of our designers and QA leads

688
00:51:15,394 --> 00:51:18,577
to regularly see their levels in action

689
00:51:18,577 --> 00:51:20,298
with brand new players.

690
00:51:20,298 --> 00:51:25,281
As our playtesters played, we uploaded metric data

691
00:51:25,281 --> 00:51:28,844
about their actions to a database over the network.

692
00:51:28,844 --> 00:51:30,705
Things like how long it took them

693
00:51:30,705 --> 00:51:32,966
to complete each part of the game,

694
00:51:32,966 --> 00:51:35,788
or how frequently they died between continue points.

695
00:51:37,218 --> 00:51:44,905
When we put that data into a spreadsheet and looked at the maximum, minimum, and median values for each point of data,

696
00:51:44,905 --> 00:51:49,910
and then color-coded cells that had values above certain targets,

697
00:51:49,910 --> 00:51:54,474
parts of the game that were potentially problematic immediately jumped out at us.

698
00:51:54,474 --> 00:52:02,121
And we could then start looking at the gameplay videos that we had recorded during the playtest sessions to investigate each potential problem.

699
00:52:03,452 --> 00:52:10,735
Notice that one poor player had to play our train yard fight 27 times before they finally

700
00:52:10,735 --> 00:52:11,135
beat it.

701
00:52:11,135 --> 00:52:13,877
That was horrifying when we saw it.

702
00:52:13,877 --> 00:52:17,078
Luckily we were able to spot that one and fix it.

703
00:52:17,078 --> 00:52:21,601
So it took a lot of energy and commitment to properly carry through with diligently

704
00:52:21,601 --> 00:52:24,122
play testing every last thing we built.

705
00:52:24,122 --> 00:52:27,223
But it was definitely worth it in terms of the quality of the game that we shipped.

706
00:52:29,456 --> 00:52:33,697
As we approached our alpha deadline, we organized a series of rolling deadlines, locking down

707
00:52:33,697 --> 00:52:37,998
the levels in small groups over the course of the four weeks leading up to each of our

708
00:52:37,998 --> 00:52:43,740
alpha, beta and gold master dates, rather than having the whole game come due on the

709
00:52:43,740 --> 00:52:45,080
same day.

710
00:52:45,080 --> 00:52:49,001
With a game as large as the one that we were making, it made good sense to do this in order

711
00:52:49,001 --> 00:52:53,502
to have fewer moving parts as we got close to the end of the project.

712
00:52:54,549 --> 00:52:59,853
We'd always planned to have long alpha and beta periods of six weeks each.

713
00:52:59,853 --> 00:53:03,956
We simply needed that much polish and bug fixing time for the size of the game

714
00:53:03,956 --> 00:53:08,539
that we'd made, and we're firm believers that allocating sufficient polish time

715
00:53:08,539 --> 00:53:11,041
can make or break a game's quality.

716
00:53:11,041 --> 00:53:18,507
However, having said that, we didn't have any time for any kind of post-production,

717
00:53:18,507 --> 00:53:23,130
and that was one last small disaster that we just had to suck up and deal with.

718
00:53:24,108 --> 00:53:28,810
Our particle artists and lighting artists and sound designers had to scramble for every

719
00:53:28,810 --> 00:53:33,371
second of polish time that they could grab, since the rest of the team, designers and

720
00:53:33,371 --> 00:53:38,593
artists in particular, were making changes and bug fixes that affected their work right

721
00:53:38,593 --> 00:53:39,414
up until the end.

722
00:53:39,414 --> 00:53:46,677
In the future, we're determined to build proper post-production time into our schedules, so

723
00:53:46,677 --> 00:53:52,599
that our games can have the level of aesthetic polish that our audience increasingly expects.

724
00:53:55,727 --> 00:54:01,812
So we hit gold master on August 20th and after that there was just the usual work to do.

725
00:54:01,812 --> 00:54:06,636
Copy editing the strategy guide and starting to look towards the press and promotion work

726
00:54:06,636 --> 00:54:10,899
for the release of the game. We were extremely happy with the way that the game had come

727
00:54:10,899 --> 00:54:15,964
together and we thought that we probably had a hit on our hands. Now all that we could

728
00:54:15,964 --> 00:54:21,248
do was wait and see how critics and the public would receive the game.

729
00:54:25,313 --> 00:54:31,099
Happily, it seems that everyone agreed with us, that Uncharted 2 Among Thieves is the

730
00:54:31,099 --> 00:54:37,185
best game that we've ever made. We're delighted to have been awarded quite staggering 33 Game

